\q1 I'll¦312821 shatter this \add ≈nation\add* and this city¦312828, just like someone¦312831 shatters a \add ≈piece of pottery¦312835\add* that can never be repaired¦312840 again¦312841. They'll bury \add ≈the dead\add* in Tofet¦312842 until \add ≈they run out of\add* room¦312845.
\v 12 Yahweh¦312855 declares that I'll¦312850 do¦312850 that to this place¦312851 and its¦312856 residents—making this city¦312860 like Tofet¦312862
\v 13 and Yerushalem's¦312866 houses \add ≈including¦312867\add* the houses of Yehudah's¦312869 kings¦312868 will be defiled like that¦312875 place¦312870, Tofet¦312871—all the houses on whose rooftops they burned incense to all the \add ≈constellations\add* and poured¦312883 out drink¦312884 offerings¦312884 to other¦312886 ‘gods¦312885’.
\p
\v 14 Then Yirmeyah returned from Tofet¦312891 where¦312892 Yahweh¦312894 had sent¦312893 him to prophesy¦312896, and he stood¦312897 in the \add ≈temple\add* courtyard¦312898 and proclaimed to all the people¦312907,
\v 15 “This is what Yisrael's god¦312915, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦312913, says¦312912: ‘Listen, every disaster that¦312933 I've¦312934 pronounced against \add @these people\add*, I'm about¦312918 to \add ≈send\add* to this city¦312922 and to all the villages around it, because¦312936 they've \add ≈been stubborn and failed to take notice\add* of my messages.’ ”
