\p
\v 1 The priest¦312952, Pashhur¦312948 (Immer's¦312951 son) who was a supervisor, heard Yirmeyah prophesying¦312962 those words¦312965 at Yahweh's¦312958 house¦312957,
\v 2 and¦312968 he struck¦312968 the prophet¦312972 Yirmeyah. Then¦312968 he placed him in the stocks¦312977 that¦312978 were at the upper¦312981 gate¦312979 of Benyamin¦312980 \add ≈hear\add* Yahweh's¦312984 house¦312983.
\v 3 The next day¦312987, when \add ≈Pashhur\add* released Yirmeyah from the stocks¦312995, Yirmeyah said¦312996 to him, “Yahweh¦313002 won't¦312999 call you ‘Pashhur’, but¦312986 ‘Magor¦313007-Missabib’ \add (which means ‘surrounded by terror’)\add*,
\v 4 because¦313011 Yahweh¦313014 says¦313013 this: Listen, I'll make¦313016 you¦313016 a terror¦313018 to yourself¦313019 and to all your friends¦313022. They'll fall¦313023 by their enemies' \add #swords\add* before your very eyes¦313026, and then I'll hand¦313034 Yehudah¦313032 over to the Babylonian king¦313035, and he'll carry them away to Babylon¦313037 and put them to \add ≈death\add*.
\v 5 I'll¦313043 give away all the wealth¦313048 of this city¦313049—all its products and valuables, and all the treasures¦313064 of Yehudah's¦313066 kings¦313065—to their enemies¦313069. They'll¦313067 plunder¦313070 it, seize it, and carry it off to Babylon¦313073.
\v 6 Then¦313075 you, Pashhur¦313076 will \add ≈be taken\add* into captivity¦313081 \add ≈along with all the others in your home\add*. You'll \add ≈be taken\add* to Babylon¦313082, and you'll die¦313085 there and be buried¦313087—you and all your friends¦313091 who you've prophesied¦313094 these lies to.
