\v 2 “Please \add ≈request\add* Yahweh's¦313339 advice on our behalf, because¦313340 the Babylonian King¦313342 Nebuchadnezzar¦313341 is \add ≈attacking\add* us. Perhaps Yahweh will do¦313348 miracles for us like \add he has in the past\add*, and will make him \add ≈stop attacking us and leave\add*.”\x + \xo 21:2: \xt 2Ki 25:1-11; 2Ch 36:17-21.\x*
