\v 3 \add ≈So\add* Yirmeyah told them to tell \add King\add* Tsidkiyah that
\v 4 Yisrael's god¦313371 Yahweh¦313370 says¦313369 this:
\m Listen, I'm about¦313374 to \add ≈make your own weapons¦313377 ineffective\add* that¦313379 you're all using to fight¦313383 the Babylonian king¦313387 and the Babylonians \add (Heb. Kasdi¦313391 = Chaldeans)\add* who are laying¦313392 siege¦313392 to you from outside¦313394 the wall¦313395, and I'll¦313396 gather¦313396 them\f + \fr 21:4 \ft This last part of the sentence is left quite literal, as it's ambiguous in the Hebrew, what or who the ‘them’ is referring to here.\f* in the middle¦313400 of this city¦313401.
\v 5 Then¦313404 I¦313405 myself will fight¦313404 you all \add ≈with all my strength and power\add* in my anger and rage and terrible fury,
\v 6 and I'll¦313416 \add ≈kill\add* this city's inhabitants¦313419—people and animals will all die¦313430 in a \add ≈terrible\add* plague.
\v 7 Then¦313432 Yahweh¦313437 declares that after¦313432 that I'll¦313438 hand over Yehudah's¦313444 King Tsidkiyah \add ≈along with\add* his officers, and the people¦313451 in this city¦313455 who survive the plague and sword and famine¦313466, to the Babylonian King Nebuchadnezzar¦313468, and to their enemies¦313473 who \add ≈want to kill them\add*. He'll \add ≈kill them with\add* the sword—he won't¦313481 spare them or show pity or compassion¦313488.
\p
\v 8 Then¦313490 you must¦313494 tell this to the people¦313492:
\m Yahweh¦313497 says¦313496 that I'm¦313498 \add ≈about to give you the choice between\add* the path to life¦313504 and¦313490 the path to death¦313508.
\v 9 Anyone¦313510 who stays in this city¦313511 will die¦313513 from \add ≈war\add*, famine¦313515, or plague, but¦313515 anyone¦313510 who goes¦313517 out and falls to their knees in front of the Babylonians who've surrounded you all, will live They'll escape with their lives \add that way\add*
\v 10 because I've¦313533 \add ≈already decided\add* to harm this city \add ≈rather than doing good\add*. Yahweh¦313542 declares that \add @this city\add* will be \add ≈handed over\add* to the Babylonian¦313546 king and he'll burn it \add down\add*.
