\q1
\v 9 As for the prophets¦314378,
\q1 \add ≈I feel broken¦314379 inside\add* and all my bones¦314385 tremble.
\q1 I've¦314386 become like a drunkard¦314388—like a man¦314390 overcome by wine,
\q1 because of Yahweh¦314394—because of his holy words¦314396.
\q1
\v 10 \add ≈Yes,\add* the land is full of adulterers¦314400—
\q1 the land mourns because¦314403 of the curse¦314406,
\q1 and the pastures¦314410 in the wilderness¦314411 have dried¦314407 up—
\q1 their course¦314413 is evil and their \add ≈power is misused\add*.
\q1
\v 11 \add ≈Yes,\add* both prophet¦314424 and priest¦314427 are \add ≈compromised\add*—
\q1 even in my house¦314431 I've¦314432 discovered their¦314433 wickedness¦314433.
