\q1 that no harm will come¦314564 to \add %them\add*.
\p
\v 18 \add ≈But¦314574\add* which of them has \add ≈attended\add* Yahweh's¦314572 council¦314571 \add meeting\add*
\q1 \add where he could\add* see \add what's happening\add* and hear his message?
\q1 Who has paid attention to his message and \add ≈obeyed it\add*?
\q1
\v 19 Listen¦314586, the storm of Yahweh's¦314589 rage¦314590 is going out,
\q1 and¦314592 the storm is \add ≈creating a whirlwind\add* that's whirling around the heads of \add ≈those who are\add* wicked¦314596.
\q1
\v 20 Yahweh's¦314603 anger¦314601 won't turn¦314600 back until¦314604 he's carried¦314609 out his \add ≈plans and\add* purposes¦314610.
\q1 In the \add ≈final\add* days¦314613, you'll all understand¦314614 it.
\p
\v 21 I didn't send \add &those\add* prophets, yet they \add ≈rushed\add* \add ?to proclaim their messages\add*.
\q1 ≈I didn't speak to them, \add ≈yet\add* they \add still\add* prophesied¦314631.
