\v 22 If they had \add in fact\add* \add ≈attended\add* my council¦314636 \add meeting\add*,
\q1 they would have proclaimed my messages to my people¦314641
\q1 and turned them back from their \add ≈wickedness and their wicked activities\add*.
\p
\v 23 Yahweh¦314654 declares:
\q1 Am I a god who's only nearby, \add ≈but¦314655\add* who isn't¦314655 \add also\add* a god from \add ≈far away\add*?
\q1
\v 24 Would someone¦314662 hide¦314661 themself in some place¦314663 and \add think\add* that I couldn't see¦314667 them? Yahweh \add ≈asks\add*.
\q1 Don't¦314665 I fill the heavens¦314674 and the earth¦314677? declares Yahweh.
\p
\v 25 Those prophets who prophesy¦314690 lies in my name¦314691, I've¦314684 heard¦314684 them say¦314693, ‘I \add ≈had a dream\add*. I \add ≈had a dream\add*!’
\v 26 How long will this go on, with prophets who prophesy¦314703 lies from their own \add ≈minds\add*, but¦314705 who are prophesying from the deceitfulness¦314706 of their own \add #hearts\add*.
\v 27 They're planning on making my people¦314713 forget¦314710 my name with the dreams¦314715 that¦314716 they report, each one to his neighbour¦314719, just as their ancestors¦314722 forgot¦314721 my name in favour of Baal's¦314726 name.
\v 28 Let the prophet¦314728 who has a dream, report \add &that\add* dream. \add ≈However,\add* the \add >one\add* who I've declared something to, let him declare my message¦314747 truthfully. What does straw¦314743 have to do with grain¦314746? That is Yahweh's¦314749 declaration.
\v 29 Isn't my message¦314753 like fire¦314754, and¦314758 like a hammer¦314758 that¦314759 shatters¦314759 rock¦314760? That is Yahweh's¦314757 declaration.
\v 30 So listen, Yahweh¦314770 declares that I'm against the prophets¦314767 who steal¦314771 my messages from \add ≈someone else\add*.
\v 31 \add ≈Yes,\add* I'm against \add &those\add* prophets¦314780 who \add ≈speak their¦314785 own messages by claim that the messages came from me\add*.
\v 32 Yahweh declares that \add ≈indeed\add*, I'm against those who prophesy¦314792 false¦314794 dreams¦314793 and retell them to lead my people astray with their reckless¦314804 lies. It wasn't me who sent or commanded them, and they're of no benefit at all to those people. That is Yahweh's¦314797 declaration.
\s1 False prophets
\rem /s1 False Prophecies and False Prophets; False Oracles and False Prophets; The Lord's Burden
\p
\v 33 \add ≈Now\add* when this people¦314825 \add group\add* or a prophet¦314829 or priest¦314832 asks you, ‘What is Yahweh's burden?’\f + \fr 23:33 \ft The Hebrew word translated ‘burden’ could alternatively mean ‘message of doom’ here and through to verse 40, except that it's also used to describe the people.\f* you \add ≈should\add* tell them, ‘\add You are the\add* burden and¦314822 I'll¦314845 abandon¦314845 you.’ That is Yahweh's declaration.
\v 34 As for the prophet¦314851 \add ≈or\add* priest¦314852 \add ≈or\add* anyone who claims that he \add ?≈knows\add* Yahweh's¦314857 burden¦314856, I'll¦314858 punish that man¦314861 and¦314851 his household¦314865.
\v 35 This is what each of you should \add ≈ask\add* their friend or relative: ‘What did Yahweh answer¦314879?’ or ‘What has Yahweh said?’
\v 36 \add ≈But¦314886\add* don't¦314888 refer anymore to Yahweh's¦314887 burden, because¦314892 each person's message¦314896 becomes the burden, so you all \add end up\add* perverting the words¦314900 of the living¦314902 god, Commander-in-chief Yahweh, our god.
\v 37 This is what you \add ≈should ask\add* to the prophet¦314911, ‘What answer¦314914 did Yahweh give you?’ or ‘What did Yahweh say?’
\v 38 \add ≈However\add* if you say, ‘Yahweh's burden’, then¦314921 this is what Yahweh says¦314928: Because you said those words, ‘Yahweh's burden,’ \add ≈after\add* I sent you all \add a message¦314934\add* saying, ‘Don't¦314941 say, “Yahweh's burden,’
\v 39 therefore listen, I'll¦314948 definitely forget you and will remove you all \add ≈out of my presence\add*—both you and your ancestors¦314959, and the city¦314955 that¦314956 I gave¦314957 you.
\v 40 Then¦314963 I'll¦314963 put permanent¦314966 shame¦314967 on you all, and¦314967 \add ≈continual insults\add* that¦314969 won't¦314970 be forgotten¦314971.
\c 24
\s1 Two baskets of figs
\rem /s1 The Good and the Bad Figs; Two Baskets of Figs; Good and Bad Figs
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 ⇔After the Babylonian King Nebuchadnezzar¦314986 had carried away Yehoyakin \add (Jehoiakim, Heb. Yekonyah = Jeconiah)\add*, son of Yehudah's King Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add*, as well as Yehudah's officials¦315001 and Yerushalem's¦315009 craftsmen¦315005 and metalsmiths, and had taken them to Babylon¦314989, Yahweh¦314975 showed¦314974 me two¦314977 baskets¦314978 of figs¦314979 placed in front¦314981 of \add *his\add* temple¦314982.\x + \xo 24:1: \xt 2Ki 24:12-16; 2Ch 36:10.\x*
\v 2 One basket of figs was very good like early¦315019, ripe figs, but¦315020 the figs in the other basket were so bad that¦315025 they \add ≈weren't edible\add*.
\v 3 Then Yahweh¦315033 asked me, “Yirmeyah, what do you see?”
\p “Figs,” I \add ≈replied\add*. “\add Some\add* figs that \add ≈look\add* very good, and \add *others\add* that are so bad \add ≈they're inedible\add*.”
\p
\v 4 Then Yahweh¦315059 \add ≈gave\add* me this message¦315057:
\v 5 Yisrael's god¦315067, Yahweh¦315066, says¦315065 this: I'll¦315074 look favourably at the exiles from Yehudah¦315078 just like those good figs¦315069, the exiles that I've¦315080 sent¦315080 out from this place¦315083 to Babylonia.
\v 6 I'll \add ≈give them my favour\add* and restore them to this land. I'll build¦315098 them up, and not tear them down. I'll plant¦315101 them, and not uproot them.
\v 7 Then¦315105 I will give¦315105 them a \add ≈desire\add* to know¦315108 me, because¦315110 I'm Yahweh¦315112. They'll be my people¦315116 and¦315105 I will be their¦315127 god¦315120, so they will turn to me \add ≈wholeheartedly\add*.
\p
\v 8 \add ≈But¦315130\add* Yahweh¦315142 declares that \add just\add* like \add &those\add* bad figs¦315130 that are \add ≈inedible\add* \add will be discarded\add*, I'll¦315144 act in that \add same\add* way towards Yehudah's¦315150 King¦315148 Zedekiah¦315147, along with his officials¦315153 and the rest of Yerushalem¦315157 who remain¦315158 in this land or go to stay in the land of Egypt¦315163.
\v 9 I'll turn them into something horrifying—a disaster, \add right there¦315182\add* in the sight of all the world's kingdoms¦315170—a disgrace and a subject for proverbs, taunts¦315174, and curses¦315175 in every place¦315178 that I'll drive them into.
\v 10 I'll¦315184 send¦315184 \add ≈armies\add*, famine¦315191, and \add ≈disease\add* against them until¦315195 they're destroyed from the land that¦315200 I gave¦315202 to them and their¦315204 ancestors¦315204.
\c 25
\s1 Exile to Babylon foretold
\rem /s1 Seventy Years of Captivity; The Babylonian Captivity Foretold; The Enemy from the North
\p
\v 1 This is the message¦315207 that¦315208 came to Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* concerning all the people¦315218 of Yehudah \add (Judah)\add* in the fourth¦315221 year of \add the reign of\add* Yehoyakim (\add Jehoiakim,\add* son of Yehudah's¦315219 King Yoshiyah \add (Josiah)\add*), which¦315208 was the first¦315230 year of \add the reign of\add* the Babylonian King Nebuchadnezzar¦315231.
\v 2 The prophet¦315238 Yirmeyah proclaimed this to all the people¦315243 \add ≈across\add* Yehudah¦315244 \add ≈including¦315245\add* all of Yerushalem's¦315249 inhabitants¦315248, saying:
\v 3 ⇔Yahweh's messages¦315272 have been coming to me for twenty-three years since the thirteenth year of the reign of Yehudah's¦315262 king Yoshiyah (\add Josiah,\add* Amon's¦315260 son), and I've¦315276 \add ≈passed them on\add* to you all \add ≈over and over again\add*, \add ≈but¦315263\add* you haven't \add ≈taken any notice\add* \add of them\add*.
\v 4 Yahweh¦315284 sent¦315283 all his servants¦315290 the prophets¦315291 to you again and¦315283 again, but¦315283 you all haven't listened¦315295 \add ≈or paid any attention\add*.
\v 5 \add ≡Those prophets\add* said, ‘Let everyone¦315308 turn¦315305 from their wicked¦315311 ways and their evil¦315310 activities, and return to the land that¦315317 Yahweh¦315319 gave¦315318 in ancient times to your ancestors¦315321 and to all of you as a permanent¦315327 \add inheritance\add*.
\v 6 \add ≈So¦315345\add* don't walk¦315331 after¦315332 other¦315334 gods¦315333 to worship¦315336 them or to bow down to them, and don't provoke¦315340 \add %him\add* with \add ≈things you make with\add* your¦315343 hands¦315343, and then¦315329 \add %he\add* won't¦315329 harm you all.’
\v 7 \add ≈But¦315348\add* Yahweh¦315354 declares that you all haven't listened¦315350 to me, \add ≈because with what you've made\add*, you've provoked¦315356 me to do harm to you.
\p
\v 8 So Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦315367 says¦315366 this: Since all of you haven't listen¦315373 to my messages,
\v 9 listen, I'm about to send¦315379 out a command to fetch¦315380 all the northern¦315386 peoples. Yahweh¦315389 declares that I will bring¦315397 my servant¦315396, the Babylonian King¦315393 Nebuchadnezzar¦315392 and \add his armies\add* against this land and its¦315404 inhabitants¦315404, and against all the nations¦315408 around you. I will \add ≈mark\add* them for destruction¦315411 and turn them into a horror—\add ≈something to be hissed at\add*, and permanent¦315416 ruins¦315415.
\v 10 I'll¦315418 put an end to the sounds of gladness¦315423 and \add ≈celebration\add*, the sounds of \add #brides\add* and \add #grooms\add*, \add and\add* the sound of the millstones and the light¦315430 of the lamp.\x + \xo 25:10: a \xt Jer 7:34; 16:9; \xo b \xt Rev 18:22-23.\x*
\v 11 Then¦315433 all of this land will become¦315433 a desolation¦315438 and a horror, and these¦315442 nations¦315441 will serve¦315440 the Babylonian¦315446 king¦315445 for seventy¦315447 years.\x + \xo 25:11: \xt 2Ch 36:21; Jer 29:10; Dan 9:2.\x*
\p
\v 12 Then¦315450 after seventy¦315452 years have \add ≈passed\add*, then¦315450 I'll¦315454 punish the king¦315457 of Babylon¦315459 and that nation¦315462—the land¦315472 of the Chaldeans—for their¦315469 wickedness, and make¦315474 it into a permanent¦315477 wasteland. That is Yahweh's¦315466 declaration.
\v 13 Then¦315479 I'll¦315479 carry out all the messages that I'd spoken¦315492 against that land, and¦315479 everything¦315495 written¦315497 in this document that Yirmeyah has prophesied¦315502 against all the nations¦315508.
\v 14 \add ≈Yes\add* many other nations and great¦315520 kings¦315519 will also make slaves out of those nations. I'll¦315521 repay¦315521 them for \add ≈everything they've done\add*.
\s1 The punishment of God of nations
\rem /s1 The Cup of God's Wrath; God's Judgment on the Nations; The Cup of the Lord's Anger
\p
\v 15 \add ≈Yes\add* Yisrael's god¦315532 Yahweh¦315531 told me, “Take this cup of the wine of fury from my hand¦315542, and all the nations¦315549 that¦315550 I'm sending¦315552 you to, make¦315543 them drink¦315543 it.
\v 16 They'll drink¦315556 and then¦315556 stagger¦315557 around and act¦315558 like mad \add >people\add* \add ≈when they see the deadly army\add* that¦315561 I'm sending out to them.
\p
\v 17 \add ≈So¦315566\add* I took¦315566 the cup from Yahweh's¦315571 hand¦315570 and¦315566 made¦315572 all the nations¦315577 that¦315578 \add *he'd\add* sent¦315580 me to, drink¦315572 from it,
\v 18 \add as well as\add* Yehudah's¦315590 cities¦315589 \add ≈including¦315587\add* Yerushalem¦315586 and its \add #king\add* and officials¦315596—to turn them into ruins and something terrifying, and into \add ≈something to hiss and curse¦315602 at\add*, as they are until this present day¦315603.
\v 19 \add Those nations included:\add*
\li1 Egypt's¦315611 King¦315609 Far'oh \add (Pharaoh¦315608)\add*, his officials¦315617, his leaders, and all his people¦315622,
\li1
\v 20 all people of mixed heritage and all the kings of the land of Uts,
\li1 all the kings of the land of Philistia: Ashkelon¦315642, Azzah \add (Gaza¦315645)\add*, Ekron¦315648, and the remnant¦315650 from Ashdod¦315651,
\li1
\v 21 Edom¦315655, Moav, and the Ammonites,
\li1
\v 22 all the kings of Tsor \add (Tyre¦315669)\add* and¦315664 Tsidon \add (Sidon¦315674)\add*,
\li1 the kings from the coastlands¦315677 across the sea,
\li1
\v 23 Dedan¦315684, Tema¦315687, Buz¦315690,
\li1 and¦315682 all who cut¦315694 the corners¦315695 \add of their hair\add*,
\li1
\v 24 all the Arabian¦315701 kings,
\li1 and¦315697 all the kings of the mixed¦315706 tribes who live in the desert,
\li1
\v 25 all the kings from Zimri¦315715, Elam¦315720, and¦315710 Media¦315725,
\li1
\v 26 all the kings¦315731 of the north¦315732, both near and¦315727 far, one after another,
\li1 all the kingdoms¦315742 \add ≈around the world\add*.
\p And after all of them, the Babylonian\f + \fr 25:26 \ft ‘Babylon’ here in the Hebrew is ‘Sheshak’, which is Hebrew for ‘Babylon’ with the letters substituted in a simple code.\f* king¦315749 will drink¦315751 \add it too\add*.
\p
\v 27 Then¦315754 Yahweh told me to tell them, ‘Yisrael's god¦315762, Commander-in-chief Yahweh, says¦315759 this: Drink and become¦315765 drunk¦315765, then¦315754 vomit¦315766, fall¦315767 down, and don't¦315768 get up \add again\add* \add ≈until the deadly army arrives\add* that¦315772 I'm sending among you.’
\v 28 Then¦315777 if any \add of the above\add* refuse¦315779 to take the cup from your hand¦315783 to drink, tell me, ‘Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦315789 says that you certainly¦315791 must¦315779 drink it,
\v 29 because listen, I'm about to bring disaster to the city¦315796 that¦315797 is called¦315798 by my name¦315800, and should you yourselves be free from punishment? You won't¦315808 be free, because I'm calling¦315813 a \add ≈deadly army\add* against all the inhabitants¦315818 of the land.’
\m That is Commander-in-chief Yahweh's¦315821 declaration.
\p
\v 30 You must¦315825 prophesy¦315825 all these¦315831 messages against them, telling them:
\q1 ‘Yahweh¦315834 will roar from the heights
\q1 and he'll \add ≈shout\add* with his voice¦315840 from his sacred¦315838 residence,
\q1 and he will roar mightily¦315841 against his \add ≈land\add*,
\q1 and he will shout, like those who tread¦315847 \add grapes in a wine-pressing pit\add*
\q1 against all those who live on the earth¦315853.
\q1
\v 31 The uproar¦315856 will \add ≈be heard even at\add* the ends of the earth¦315860
\q1 because¦315861 Yahweh¦315863 brings a charge against the nations¦315864.
\q1 He \add ≈will pass\add* judgment on all humankind
\q1 and \add ≈have the wicked¦315870 killed in war\add*.
\m That is Yahweh's¦315863 declaration.
\p
\v 32 Commander-in-chief says this:
\q1 Listen, disaster is spreading from nation to nation.
\q1 A \add ≈terrible\add* storm¦315889 is rising from the ends of the earth¦315894.
\m
\v 33 Then¦315896 those¦315897 killed that day¦315899 by Yahweh¦315898 will be spread from \add one\add* end of the earth to the other. They won't¦315907 be mourned¦315908 \add over\add*, gathered¦315910, or buried¦315912—they'll be like dung lying on the ground.
\p
\v 34 Wail, \add you\add* shepherds¦315921, and call out for help.
\q1 Roll around in the dust, \add you\add* leaders of the flock¦315925,
\q1 because¦315926 the \add ≈time¦315929\add* has come for your slaughter¦315930.
\q1 You'll all be scattered when you fall¦315932, like \add fragments of broken\add* pottery.
\q1
\v 35 There's no safe place¦315937 for the shepherds¦315940 \add to go to\add*.
\q1 ≈There'll be no escape for the leaders of the flock¦315943.
\q1
\v 36 Hear the shepherds' cries of distrress¦315946
\q1 ≈and¦315948 the wails of the leaders of the flock¦315950,
\q1 →because Yahweh¦315954 is destroying¦315953 their¦315957 \add #pastures\add*.
\q1
\v 37 So¦315959 the peaceful¦315961 pastures¦315960 will be devastated¦315959
\q1 \add ≈because of\add* Yahweh's¦315966 \add ≈fierce\add* anger¦315964.
\q1
\v 38 He's left his den like a young lion would,
\q1 because¦315979 their¦315974 land will become¦315973 a horror
\q1 due to the oppressor's¦315978 anger and \add @Yahweh's\add* fierce angry.
\c 26
\s1 Wanting a death sentence for Yirmeyah
\rem /s1 Jeremiah's Prophecies in the Temple; Jeremiah Threatened With Death; Jeremiah Is Brought to Trial; Jeremiah's Escape from Death
\p
\v 1 \add ≈Near\add* the beginning¦315984 of the reign of Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim, Yoshiyah's\add*/Josiah's son), this message¦315993 came¦315992 from Yahweh¦315996:
\v 2 Yahweh¦316002 says this: Stand in the courtyard¦316004 of my \add ≈temple\add* and speak about all of Yehudah's¦316014 cities¦316013 who come to worship¦316016 at my \add ≈residence\add*. Proclaim all the messages¦316031 that¦316024 I've commanded¦316025 you to say to them—don't¦316028 hold \add ≈anything\add* back.
\v 3 Maybe they'll listen¦316034 and everyone¦316036 will turn from \add #their wicked ways\add*, and then I would turn back the disaster that¦316043 I'm planning¦316045 to \add ≈send\add* to them because of their wicked \add ≈behaviour\add*,
\v 4 \add ≈so\add* you \add need to\add* tell them that Yahweh¦316056 says¦316055 this:
\m If you don't¦316059 listen¦316060 to me so as to \add ≈follow my instructions that I've¦316065 given to\add* you all,
\v 5 \add ≡if you don't¦316080\add* listen¦316068 to the words¦316071 of my servants¦316072 the prophets¦316073 that I've¦316075 been \add regularly\add* sending to you, and \add indeed\add* you haven't listened¦316081,
\v 6 then¦316083 I'll \add ≈destroy\add* this house¦316086 like \add I did at\add* Shiloh¦316088\x + \xo 26:6: \xt Josh 18:1; Psa 78:60; Jer 7:12-14.\x* and¦316083 I'll turn this city¦316091 into a curse¦316095 to/for all the nations¦316097 \add ≈in the world\add*.
\p
\v 7 The priests¦316102, the prophets¦316103, and all the people¦316106 heard¦316101 Yirmeyah proclaiming those words¦316113 at Yahweh's¦316116 \add ≈temple\add*.
\v 8 Then¦316118 as soon as Yirmeyah¦316121 had finished¦316120 saying everything that Yahweh¦316129 had commanded¦316128 him to tell all the people, the priests¦316138 and the prophets¦316139 and all the people seized¦316136 him \add ≈and threatened to kill him, saying\add*:
\v 9 Why have you¦316148 prophesied¦316148 in Yahweh's name¦316149 and said that this \add ≈temple\add* will be \add destroyed\add* like Shiloh¦316153, and that this city¦316157 will become desolate¦316159, with no \add #inhabitants\add*?” Then all the people¦316165 \add ≈gathered together\add* against Yirmeyah at Yahweh's \add ≈residence\add*.
\p
\v 10 Then¦316172 Yehudah's¦316175 officials¦316174 heard¦316172 \add ≈about what was going on\add*, and¦316172 they went¦316179 up from the \add ≈palace\add* to \add ≈the temple where\add* they sat in the gateway at the New Gate at Yahweh's¦316184 \add ≈residence\add*.
\v 11 Then the priests¦316194 and the prophets spoke to the officials¦316198 and to all the people¦316203, saying, “It's right for this man¦316208 to die, because¦316210 he prophesied¦316211 against¦316212 this city¦316214, as you've all heard¦316217 with your own ears¦316218.”
\p
\v 12 \add ≈So¦316220\add* Yirmeyah¦316221 spoke to all the officials¦316226 and all the people¦316231 and said¦316220, “Yahweh¦316233 has sent¦316234 me out to prophesy¦316235 to say¦316232 all the words¦316247 that¦316248 you have heard¦316249, against¦316236 \add both\add* this \add ≈temple\add* and this city¦316242.
\v 13 \add ≈So¦316251 now,\add* improve your ways¦316253 and your \add ≈practices\add*, and listen¦316255 to the voice¦316256 of your god¦316258 Yahweh¦316257 so that he'll relent concerning¦316261 the disaster that he's proclaimed against you all.
\v 14 \add ≈As for me,\add* here I am in your \add #hands\add*—do¦316271 to me \add ≈whatever you think\add* is right¦316275 and¦316268 proper.
\v 15 \add ≈However,\add* you must¦316281 surely know that if you kill me, then you're all bringing innocent¦316291 blood¦316290 on yourselves¦316294 and on this city¦316297 and its inhabitants¦316301, because¦316282 Yahweh¦316305 has truly sent me to you to proclaim all these¦316313 messages for you all \add ≈to hear\add*.”
\p
\v 16 Then the officials¦316317 and all the people¦316320 said¦316316 to the priests¦316323 and to the prophets¦316326, “This man¦316329 \add ≈doesn't deserve to be sentenced¦316331 to\add* death¦316333, because¦316334 he's spoken¦316338 to us in the name¦316335 of our¦316337 god¦316337, Yahweh¦316336.”
\p
\v 17 Then¦316341 \add ≈some\add* of \add Yehudah's\add* elders¦316343 \add ≈stepped forward\add* and¦316341 spoke to all the people¦316351 who were gathered there,
\v 18 “Micah (\add Heb. Mikah,\add* the Morashtite) prophesied¦316358 \add ≈during the lifetime\add* of Yehudah's¦316363 King¦316361 Hizkiyah\add (Hezekiah)\add*, and he told all the people¦316369 from Yehudah that Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦316376 says¦316374 this:
\q1 Tsiyyon¦316378 \add (Zion¦316378)\add*, a field¦316379 will be ploughed,
\q1 and Yerushalem¦316381 will become heaps¦316382 \add of ruins¦316382\add*,
\q1 and the \add ≈temple\add* hill¦316384 will become an \add ≈overgrown\add* forest¦316387.\x + \xo 26:18: \xt Mic 3:12.\x*
\m
\v 19 Did Yehudah's¦316394 King¦316392 Hizkiyah or anyone else in Yehudah put him to death? Didn't \add @Hizkiyah\add* \add ≈respect and honour\add* Yahweh and \add ≈ask for\add* \add *his\add* favour, and didn't¦316398 Yahweh \add ≈relent from sending\add* the disaster that he had pronounced against them? \add ≈It seems that\add* we're about¦316418 to bring great¦316420 \add ≈harm\add* on ourselves.”
\p
\v 20 \add ≈Now\add* there was \add ≈another\add* man¦316427 prophesying¦316429 in Yahweh's¦316431 name¦316430 of Yahweh: Uriyah (son of Shemayah¦316435 from Kiriat-Yearim) who prophesied¦316438 against this city¦316441 and¦316425 against this land \add ≈with similar\add* messages to Yirmeyah.
\v 21 \add ≈When¦316451\add* King¦316452 Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add* and all his warriors¦316457 and all the officials¦316460 heard his words¦316463, the king \add ≈wanted\add* to put him to death¦316466. \add ≈However when\add* Uriyah heard \add >about it\add*, he became afraid¦316469, and he fled and went to Egypt¦316472 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.
\v 22 \add ≈However,\add* King¦316475 Yehoyakim sent sent Akbor's son Elnatan¦316480 and¦316474 several other men to Egypt¦316478 \add to get Uriyah\add*.
\v 23 They brought¦316490 Uriyah back from Egypt¦316494 and took¦316495 him to King¦316498 Yehoyakim \add ≈who ran him through with a sword¦316501\add* and threw¦316502 his corpse¦316505 into the \add ≈public graveyard¦316508\add*.
\p
\v 24 However, Shafan's¦316517 son Ahikam¦316514 \add ≈supported\add* Yirmeyah and \add ≈didn't¦316522 allow the people¦316528 to kill him¦316529\add*.
\c 27
\s1 Yirmeyah wears a yoke
\rem /s1 Jeremiah opposes false prophets; The Sign of the Yoke; Jeremiah Wears an Ox Yoke; Judah to Serve Nebuchadnezzar
\p
\v 1 At the beginning¦316532 of the reign¦316533 of Yehudah's¦316539 King¦316538 Yehoyakim (\add Jehoiakim\add*, son of Yoshiyah \add Josiah\add*), this message¦316541 came¦316540 to Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* from Yahweh¦316547,\x + \xo 27:1: \xt 2Ki 24:18-20; 2Ch 36:11-13.\x*
\v 2 telling \add %him\add* this:
\m Make¦316553 yourself¦316556 a wooden \add ox\add* yoke with bars, and \add ≈tie\add* it to your¦316562 neck.
\v 3 \add ≈Use it to send¦316564 messages\add* to the kings of Edom¦316568, Moab¦316572, Ammon¦316577, Tsor \add (Tyre¦316581)\add*, and¦316564 Tsidon \add (Sidon¦316585)\add*, \add ≈through the ambassadors\add* \add from those countries\add* who've come to Yerushalem¦316589 to \add meet with\add* King¦316567 Tsidkiyah \add (Zedekiah¦316592)\add*
\v 4 to tell them that Yisrael's¦316608 god¦316607, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦316605 says to give their¦316600 masters this message:
\v 5 I myself made¦316616 the earth \add and\add* the \add #people\add* and \add #animals\add* that¦316626 are on the earth, by my \add ≈direct actions\add* and my great¦316632 strength, and I give¦316635 it to whoever \add ≈see fit\add*.
\v 6 Now I've \add ≈personally handed over\add* all these¦316648 lands¦316647 to my servant¦316654, the Babylonian King¦316651 Nebuchadnezzar¦316650, and¦316640 I've also given the animals¦316658 in the countryside¦316659 to him to serve¦316662 him.
\v 7 All the nations will serve him and his son and then his \add ≈grandson\add*, until¦316677 the time of his own land¦316681 comes¦316678 \add due\add*. \add ≈Yes, it will\add*, and then many nations and great¦316690 kings¦316689 will make him serve them.
\p
\v 8 Any nation or kingdom¦316694 that won't serve¦316698 the Babylonian King Nebuchadnezzar and that won't put its neck into his yoke, then¦316692 I'll¦316720 punish that nation with \add ≈war\add* and famine¦316718 and \add ≈disease\add* until¦316728 I've¦316730 used \add @King Nebuchadnezzar\add* to finish them \add off\add*. That is Yahweh's¦316727 declaration,
\v 9 \add ≈so\add* don't¦316735 you all keep listening¦316737 to your ‘prophets¦316740’, and to your diviners¦316743 and dreamers¦316745, and to your soothsayers¦316748 and sorcerers¦316751—all those who keep telling you that you all won't¦316735 serve¦316759 the Babylonian¦316763 king¦316762,
\v 10 because they're prophesying¦316768 lies to you, so as to remove¦316771 you all far away from on your land. \add ≈Yes,\add* I will drive¦316775 you all out and you'll die \add in a foreign land\add*.
\v 11 \add ≈However,\add* the nation that brings¦316781 its neck into the Babylonian king's yoke and serves¦316789 him, I'll¦316790 let \add @that nation\add* remain¦316790 on its land¦316793, and it will cultivate it and live \add ≈there\add*. That's is Yahweh's¦316796 declaration.
\p
\v 12 Then¦316801 to Yehudah's¦316806 King¦316804 Tsidkiyah \add (Zedekiah¦316803)\add*, I \add ≈passed on\add* those \add same\add* words¦316810, saying, “Put your necks¦316816 into the yoke of the Babylonian king, and serve¦316821 him and his people¦316823, and live.
\v 13 Why would you¦316828 and your¦316829 people¦316829 die¦316827 from \add ≈war\add*, famine¦316831, and \add ≈disease\add*, as Yahweh¦316835 has \add ≈said will come to any\add* nation¦316838 that¦316839 doesn't serve¦316842 the Babylonian king¦316845?
\v 14 \add ≈So¦316848\add* don't¦316848 listen¦316850 to the messages from the prophets who are speaking to you when they tell you all not to serve¦316859 the king¦316862 of Babylon¦316863 as they're prophesying¦316867 lies to you
\v 15 because I didn't¦316871 send them. Yahweh¦316875 declares that they're using my name¦316878 to prophesy lies so that I'll drive¦316881 you out, and you'll all perish¦316883—\add both\add* you and the prophets who are prophesying to you.”
\v 16 Then¦316889 I told the priests¦316891 and all those people¦316896 that Yahweh says¦316901: Don't¦316903 listen¦316905 to the words¦316908 of your prophets who are prophesying to you and saying that the utensils from Yahweh's¦316902 \add ≈temple\add* will \add ≈soon\add* be brought¦316918 back from Babylon¦316919, because¦316922 they're prophesying lies to you.
\v 17 Don't¦316928 listen¦316930 to them. Serve the Babylonian king¦316935 and¦316938 live¦316938. Why should this city¦316941 become¦316940 a ruin¦316943?
\v 18 If they¦316948 were prophets¦316947 \add ≈who really have access to\add* Yahweh's message¦316952, then¦316945 please¦316958 let them intercede with Commander-in-chief Yahweh so that¦316966 the utensils remaining¦316966 in Yahweh's \add ≈temple\add* and in Yehudah's¦316972 king's \add ≈palace\add* and in Yerushalem¦316973 \add ≈don't¦316961 end up being taken\add* to Babylon¦316974.
\p
\v 19 \add ≈Yes,\add* Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦316980 has spoken about the \add bronze\add* pillars¦316984 and the \add large, bronze\add* \add ≈water basin\add*, and concerning¦316982 the \add bronze\add* stands¦316990 and the rest of the utensils remaining¦316992 in this city¦316995,
\v 20 which the Babylonian King Nebuchadnezzar¦317002 didn't¦316999 take when he exiled¦317005 Yehudah's¦317015 King Yekonyah (\add Jeconiah,\add* son of \add Yehoyakim/\add*Jehoiakim) from Yerushalem to Babylon¦317004, along with all the nobles¦317021 of Yehudah including¦317018 Yerushalem.
\v 21 Yisrael's god¦317031, Commander-in-chief Yahweh says¦317028 about the utensils remaining¦317036 in Yahweh's¦317029 \add ≈temple\add* and in the \add ≈palace\add* of the king¦317040 of Yehudah¦317042 and Yerushalem¦317043:
\v 22 They'll be taken¦317046 to Babylon and they'll remain¦317048 there¦317047 until¦317049 the \add ≈time when I punish\add* \add @those Babylonians\add*, and then I'll¦317056 bring them \add ≈back\add* and restore them to this place¦317060. That is Yahweh's¦317055 declaration.
\c 28
\s1 Yirmeyah vs Prophet Hananyah
\rem /s1 Jeremiah Condemns Hananiah; The False Prophet Hananiah; Jeremiah and the Prophet Hananiah; Hananiah Opposes Jeremiah and Dies
\p
\v 1 In the fifth¦317078 month¦317077 of the fourth¦317076 year of the reign¦317069 of Yehudah's¦317073 King¦317071 Tsidkiyah \add (Zedekiah¦317070)\add*, Azzur's¦317084 son Hananyah¦317081 who was a ‘prophet¦317085’ from Gibeon¦317087, said to me in Yahweh's¦317089 \add ≈temple\add* as priests¦317091 and all the people¦317094 \add watched\add*, saying,\x + \xo 28:1: \xt 2Ki 24:18-20; 2Ch 36:11-13.\x*
\v 2 “Yisrael's god¦317102, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦317100 says¦317099: I've broken the yoke of the Babylonian king¦317109.
\v 3 Within two years¦317114, I, myself, will bring¦317117 back here all the utensils from Yahweh's¦317128 residence that¦317129 the Babylonian King¦317133 Nebuchadnezzar¦317131 got from this place and took to Babylon¦317135.
\v 4 I, myself, will \add ≈also\add* bring¦317161 Yekonyah (\add Jeconiah,\add* the son of Yehudah's¦317151 King¦317149 Yehoyakim/\add Jehoiakim\add*) back to this place¦317164, and¦317143 all the exiles¦317156 from Yehudah that were taken to Babylon¦317159, because¦317169 I'll¦317160 break¦317170 the yoke of the Babylonian king. That is Yahweh's¦317168 declaration.”
\p
\v 5 Then¦317177 the prophet Yirmeyah¦317178 spoke to the prophet Hananyah¦317182, as the priests¦317185 and¦317186 all the people¦317189 standing¦317190 in Yahweh's¦317192 \add ≈temple\add* \add ≈watched\add*,
\v 6 saying, “Let it be so—may Yahweh do¦317199 all that. May Yahweh \add ≈confirm\add* your¦317205 messages that you¦317207 prophesied¦317196, to bring¦317208 the \add ≈temple utensils\add* back to this place¦317219, along with all the exiles¦317215 from Babylon¦317216.
\v 7 However, please¦317226 listen to this message¦317227 that¦317229 I, myself, am speaking¦317231 \add ≈as you and all the people¦317236 listen\add*:
\v 8 The prophets who \add ≈preceded\add* \add both\add* me and you¦317242, prophesied¦317246 \add ≈long ago\add* that many \add ≈nations\add* and powerful kingdoms¦317253 would experience wars, \add ≈terrible suffering\add*, and \add ≈deadly diseases\add*.
\v 9 The prophet who prophesies¦317261 about peace¦317262, \add &that\add* prophet will be known as ‘a truthful¦317272 prophet sent¦317270 by Yahweh¦317271’ \add only\add* when his message¦317264 comes¦317263 \add to pass\add*.”
\p
\v 10 Then¦317274 the prophet Hananyah¦317275 took¦317274 the yoke bar off the prophet Yirmeyah's¦317282 neck, and¦317274 broke¦317284 it.
\v 11 Then as all the people¦317291 watched, he said¦317286, “This is what Yahweh¦317295 says¦317294: Just like that, I'll¦317297 break¦317297 the yoke of the Babylonian King¦317303 Nebuchadnezzar¦317302 off the neck of all the nations¦317314 within two¦317307 more years¦317307.”
\p Then the prophet¦317317 Yirmeyah \add ≈left the gathering\add*.
\p
\v 12 ⇔After the prophet Hananyah¦317330 broke¦317329 the yoke bar that had been on the prophet Yirmeyah's neck, Yahweh's¦317324 message¦317322 came to Yirmeyah saying,
\v 13 “Go and tell Hananyah¦317345 this: ‘Yahweh¦317349 says¦317348 that you've¦317352 broken¦317352 wooden yoke bars, but¦317342 in their¦317354 place¦317354, you'll make¦317353 yoke bars out of iron,’
\v 14 because Yisrael's god¦317364, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦317362 says¦317361, ‘I've put an iron yoke bar on the neck of all these¦317376 nations¦317375 to serve the Babylonian King¦317381 Nebuchadnezzar¦317380, and they will \add indeed\add* serve him. I've also given¦317390 him the animals¦317388 from the countryside¦317389.’ ”
\p
\v 15 Then¦317393 the prophet Yirmeyah told the prophet Hananyah, “Listen, please¦317402, Hananyah. Yahweh¦317407 hasn't sent¦317406 you, and¦317393 you yourself have made¦317409 this people¦317412 \add group\add* \add ≈put their trust in things that aren't¦317404 true\add*.
\v 16 Because of that, Yahweh says¦317420 this: ‘Listen, I'm \add ≈removing you from this world\add*. \add ≈You'll die¦317429 this very\add* year¦317427, because¦317430 you have \add ≈said things that would cause the people to rebel¦317432\add* against¦317434 Yahweh.’ ”
\p
\v 17 The prophet¦317440 Hananyah¦317439 then¦317438 died¦317438 in the seventh¦317444 month¦317443 of that year¦317441.
\c 29
\s1 Yirmeyah's letter to the exiled Jews
\rem /s1 Jeremiah's Letter to the Exiles in Babylon; Jeremiah's Letter to the Jews in Babylonia
\p
\v 1 The prophet Yirmeyah sent¦317451 a \add ≈letter¦317449\add* from Yerushalem to the remainder¦317457 of the elders¦317458 of the exile, and to the priests¦317462, and to the prophets, and to all the people¦317470 that¦317450 Nebuchadnezzar¦317473 had exiled from Yerushalem to Babylon¦317475\x + \xo 29:1-2: \xt 2Ki 24:12-16; 2Ch 36:10.\x*
\v 2 after the \add ≈removal\add* from Yerushalem of King¦317481 Yekonyah \add (Jeconiah)\add* and the queen¦317482 mother, the \add ≈court¦317483 officials¦317484\add* and the leaders of Yehudah¦317485 and Yerushalem, plus¦317482 the craftsmen¦317487 and the metalsmiths.
\v 3 \add He sent it\add* with Shafan's¦317495 son Elasah¦317492 and Hilkiyah's son Gemaryah¦317496, who Yehudah's¦317505 King Tsidkiyah \add (Zedekiah¦317502)\add* sent to the Babylonian King Nebuchadnezzar¦317508 in Babylon¦317510. \add The letter\add* said,
\pi1
\v 4 Yisrael's god¦317519, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦317517 says¦317516 this to all \add ≈of you\add* that I've exiled¦317523 from Yerushalem¦317527 to Babylon¦317528:
\v 5 Build¦317530 houses¦317531 and live in them, and plant¦317533 gardens¦317534 and eat¦317535 their¦317538 fruit.
\v 6 \add ≈Marry\add* and \add ≈have children\add*. \add ≈Find\add* wives for your sons and give your daughters \add ≈in marriage\add* so that they \add also\add* \add ≈have children\add*. \add ≈Increase in number\add* there¦317558—don't¦317559 become fewer.
\v 7 \add ≈In addition¦317563, the city¦317567 that I've¦317569 sent¦317569 you all into exile¦317569 to, work to make it more prosperous\add* and¦317563 pray to Yahweh¦317576 for it, because¦317577 \add ≈if it prospers, its prosperity will belong¦317579 to all of you\add*.
\v 8 That's because¦317584 Yisrael's god¦317589, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦317587 says¦317586 this: Don't¦317591 let your prophets¦317595 and diviners¦317599 who are among you deceive¦317593 you, and don't¦317591 listen¦317602 to your dreams¦317605 that¦317606 you \add wishfully\add* dream,
\v 9 because \add @those prophets\add* are prophesying¦317613 \add ≈using\add* my name¦317615 \add ≈but not being truthful\add*—I didn't¦317616 send them. That is Yahweh's¦317620 declaration.
\p
\v 10 “Because this is what Yahweh¦317627 says¦317626: When seventy¦317632 years \add ≈have passed\add* for Babylon¦317631, I'll visit \add ≈take notice of you all\add* \add again\add*, and¦317636 I'll \add ≈implement\add* my good¦317641 message¦317640 about you—to bring¦317642 you all back to this place¦317646,\x + \xo 29:10: \xt 2Ch 36:21; Jer 25:11; Dan 9:2.\x*
\v 11 because I know¦317651 the plans that¦317655 I \add ≈have\add* for you all: plans for peaceful well-being—not to bring you all harm, \add but¦317664 rather\add* a future¦317668 \add ≈with\add* hope. That is Yahweh's¦317661 declaration.
\v 12 Then¦317671 you'll all call¦317671 out to me \add for help\add*, and you'll come¦317673 and pray to me, and I'll¦317676 listen¦317676 to you all.
\v 13 You'll search¦317679 for me, and¦317681 you'll find me, because¦317682 you'll all \add ≈want to follow me with complete sincerity\add*.\x + \xo 29:13: \xt Deu 4:29.\x*
\v 14 Then¦317688, Yahweh has declared, I'll let myself¦317688 be found¦317688 by you all, and I'll \add ≈bring you back from\add* captivity¦317696. I'll gather¦317698 you all from all the nations¦317702 and all the places¦317705 that I banished¦317707 you to, and I'll bring you all back to the place¦317717 that I sent you into exile¦317720 from. That is Yahweh's¦317692 declaration.
\pi1
\v 15 Because you've all said¦317725 that Yahweh¦317728 has \add ≈appointed\add* prophets¦317729 for \add %you\add* \add there\add* in Babylon¦317730,
\v 16 \add ≈then\add* Yahweh¦317738 \add ≈has something to say\add* about the king¦317741 sitting on David's¦317746 throne¦317745 and¦317747 about all the people¦317751 living in this city¦317753—your relatives who didn't¦317757 go into exile¦317761 with you.
\v 17 So Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦317765 says¦317764: Listen, I'm about¦317768 to send¦317768 \add ≈war\add*, famine¦317775 and \add ≈deadly diseases\add* against them. I'll¦317779 make¦317779 them like rotten¦317782 figs¦317781 that¦317783 are so bad they're \add ≈inedible\add*.
\v 18 \add ≈Yes,\add* I'll chase after¦317790 them with \add ≈war\add*, famine¦317792, and \add ≈deadly diseases\add*, and I'll make¦317794 them become a horror to all the \add ≈world's\add* kingdoms¦317799—a curse¦317801 and a desolation, and a reproach¦317804 and \add ≈something to be hissed at\add* by all the nations¦317807 where¦317808 I've¦317810 driven them,
\v 19 because they¦317818 didn't listen to my messages that¦317825 I sent¦317826 to them \add ≈over and over again\add* via my servants¦317830 the prophets¦317831, but¦317833 all you \add exiles\add* didn't listen. That is Yahweh's¦317824 declaration.
\p
\v 20 \add ≈But¦317840\add* all you exiles¦317847 that I sent¦317850 away from Yerushalem¦317851 to Babylon¦317852, listen¦317841 to Yahweh's¦317844 message¦317842:
\pi1
\v 21 Yisrael's god¦317860, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦317858, says¦317857 this about¦317880 Kolayah's¦317867 son Ahav and Maaseyah's¦317873 son Tsidkiyah, who are \add both\add* prophesying¦317874 untruths to you in my name¦317876: Listen, I'm \add ≈handing them over\add* to the Babylonian King¦317884 Nebuchadnezzar¦317883, and he'll \add ≈kill them right in front of you\add*.
\v 22 Then¦317890 because of them, a \add new\add* curse¦317892 \add phrase\add* will be taken¦317890 on by all the \add ≈Jewish\add* exiles¦317894 in Babylon¦317897, which goes, “May Yahweh¦317900 make¦317899 you¦317899 like Tsidkiyah and¦317902 Ahav, who were roasted¦317905 in the fire¦317909 by the Babylonian king¦317906,”
\v 23 because they did¦317913 something shameful in Yisrael¦317915 and they have committed¦317916 adultery¦317916 with the wives¦317919 of their neighbours¦317920, and they spoke¦317921 untrue messages¦317922 in my name¦317923 that I hadn't commanded¦317927 them to. I am the one \add ≈who knows that\add* and I'm a witness¦317933. That is Yahweh's¦317936 declaration.
\s1 Message to false prophet Shemayah
\rem /s1 A Message for Shemaiah; Message to Shemaiah; The Letter of Shemaiah
\p
\v 24 \add Yahweh told me to\add* tell Shemayah¦317941 (the Nehelamite¦317942) this:
\v 25 Yisrael's god¦317951, Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦317949 says¦317948 this: Because you sent¦317957 letters¦317959 in your name¦317958 to all the people¦317964 in Yerushalem¦317966, and to the priest¦317973 Tsefanyah (Maaseyah's¦317972 son), and to all the priests¦317977, to tell \add <Tsefanyah\add*:
\pi1
\v 26 Yahweh has made you, \add Tsefanyah,\add* priest in place¦317983 of the priest Yehoyada \add (Jehoiada)\add*, to be \add #overseer\add* in Yahweh's¦317980 \add ≈temple\add* over every man who raves \add out loud\add*, making himself a prophet¦317994, and you must¦317995 put him in the stocks¦317999 \add ≈with an iron collar¦318002 around his\add* neck.
\v 27 \add ≈So¦318004 why\add* haven't you rebuked¦318007 Yirmeyah the Antotite who's prophesying¦318010 to you all,
\v 28 because he's sent¦318017 \add a letter\add* to us \add here\add* in Babylon¦318019 saying, “\add @Your exile\add* \add ≈will last a long¦318021 time\add*. Build houses¦318024 and live in them. Plant gardens¦318027 and eat¦318028 their¦318031 fruit.”
\p
\v 29 The priest¦318035 Tsefanyah read that letter¦318038 to the prophet¦318042 Yirmeyah,
\v 30 then Yahweh¦318048 \add ≈gave\add* this message¦318046 to Yirmeyah¦318051:
\v 31 Send to all the \add #exiles\add* to tell them: This is what Yahweh¦318063 says¦318062 about Shemayah the Nehelamite¦318067: Because Shemayah has prophesied¦318070 to you all, \add ≈even though\add* I didn't¦318074 send him, and he made¦318076 you trust \add ≈what's not true\add*,
\v 32 therefore Yahweh says this: Listen, I \add ≈will punish\add* Shemayah¦318091 the Nehelamite¦318092 and \add ≈his descendants\add*. \add ≈None of his family\add* will live among this people, and \add ≈he won't¦318096 experience the good things\add* that¦318112 I'll¦318114 do for my people, because¦318121 he's \add ≈encouraged\add* rebellion¦318123 against Yahweh. That is Yahweh's¦318086 declaration.
\c 30
\s1 Yahweh's promises to his people
\rem /s1 The Lord's Promises to His People; Restoration of Israel; Promises of Deliverance; Promises of restoration for the people; Restoration Promised for Israel and Judah
\p
\v 1 Yahweh¦318137 \add ≈gave\add* Yirmeyah¦318135 a message¦318130, saying:
\v 2 Yisrael's god¦318144, Yahweh¦318143 says¦318142 this: Write down on a scroll all the messages that¦318154 I've¦318156 \add ≈given\add* you¦318157,
\v 3 because listen to Yahweh's¦318168 declaration: The \add ≈time¦318164\add* is coming¦318165 when I'll restore my people¦318173 of Yisrael¦318174 and Yehudah from captivity¦318172, and I'll bring¦318178 them back to the land that¦318182 I have to their¦318185 ancestors¦318185, and they'll \add ≈take¦318186 possession¦318186 of it¦318186\add* \add again\add*.
\p
\v 4 \add ≈Now\add* these¦318189 are the messages that¦318191 Yahweh¦318193 spoke¦318192 concerning¦318194 Yisrael¦318196 and Yehudah¦318199:
\q1
\v 5 \add ≈Yes,\add* Yahweh¦318205 says¦318204 this:
\q1 A \add ≈cry of panic and terror\add* has been heard¦318208,
\q1 ≈and there's¦318210 no peace¦318211.
\q1
\v 6 Please ask and \add ≈find out\add*: can \add #males\add* give birth?
\q1 Why do I see every strong man with his hands¦318226 on his \add ≈hips\add* like a woman \add ≈in labour\add*?
\q1 And \add ≡why has\add* \add ≈everyone's faces¦318234 gone so pale\add*?
\q1
\v 7 Oh dear, \add ≈that will be a terrible day¦318240 like nothing that's come before\add*.
\q1 ≈It'll be a distressing¦318246 time¦318244 for Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*,
\q1 →\add ≈but\add* he'll be rescued from it.
\p
\v 8 Then¦318252 Commander-in-chief Yahweh¦318257 declares that \add ≈at that time\add* I'll break¦318259 his yoke off your neck, and I'll \add ≈pull\add* your \add ≈chains\add* apart¦318264, and foreigners will no longer enslave \add @your country\add*.
\v 9 Then¦318273 they'll serve¦318273 their god¦318276 Yahweh¦318275, and¦318273 their king¦318279 \add on David's¦318278 throne\add* who I'll¦318281 appoint for them.
\p
\v 10 Then Yahweh¦318293 declares:
\q1 Then you, my servant¦318289 Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*, don't be afraid,
\q1 ≈and don't be dismayed¦318296, Yisrael \add (Israel¦318297)\add*,
\q1 because¦318298 listen, I'm rescuing you from afar,
\q1 and your offspring from the land \add ≈where they were held captive¦318306\add*.
\q1 \add ≈Yisrael\add* will return¦318307 and be left alone and at ease,
\q1 and there¦318311 won't¦318286 be anyone¦318312 making it afraid.\x + \xo 30:10-11: \xt Jer 46:27-28.\x*
\q1
\v 11 Yahweh¦318320 declares:
\q1 \add ≈Yes,\add* I'm with you to rescue you,
\q1 because¦318322 I'll \add ≈completely destroy\add* all the nations¦318327 that I've¦318330 scattered¦318330 you to,
\q1 but I won't \add ≈completely destroy\add* you.
\q1 I'll discipline¦318338 you according to justice¦318339,
\q1 \add ≈but I won't just let you off what you deserve\add*.
\p
\v 12 \add ≈Yes,\add* Yahweh¦318348 says¦318347 this:
\q1 Your fracture¦318350 is incurable¦318349.
\q1 ≈Your wound¦318352 is severe¦318351.
\q1
\v 13 There's no one pleading¦318356 your cause¦318357.
\q1 There's no medicines¦318359 for your wound.
\q1 ≈There's no healing¦318360 for you.
\q1
\v 14 All your lovers¦318366 have forgotten¦318367 you—
\q1 ≈they don't¦318369 care about you.
\q1 \add ≈Yes,\add* I've¦318374 struck¦318374 you \add ≈like an enemy¦318373 would\add*,
\q1 ≈with the discipline of a cruel¦318376 \add >person\add*,
\q1 due to the \add ≈severity of your wickedness\add*.
\q1 ≈You've \add ≈disobeyed so frequently\add*.
\q1
\v 15 Why do¦318385 you cry¦318385 out about your fracture¦318388—
\q1 ≈about your incurable¦318389 pain?
\q1 Your \add ≈wickedness has been severe\add*.
\q1 ≈You've \add ≈disobeyed so often\add*
\q1 →\add so\add* I've¦318397 done¦318397 those things to you.
\q1
\v 16 \add ≈Because of that\add*, all those who devoured you will be devoured,
\q1 ≈and all of your adversaries, every one of them, will go¦318411 into captivity¦318410.
\q1 Then the ones plundering you will become like plunder,
\q1 ≈and all those preying on you, I'll¦318418 give \add >to you\add* as spoil¦318419.
\q1
\v 17 \add ≈Yes,\add* I'll bring¦318422 healing¦318423 to you,
\q1 and I'll heal¦318426 you from your wounds¦318425
\q1 because¦318430 they've called¦318432 you an outcast.
\q1 ‘She is Tsiyyon¦318434 \add (Zion¦318434)\add*—no one cares¦318436 about her.’
\q1 That is Yahweh's¦318429 declaration.
\p
\v 18 Yahweh¦318444 says¦318443 this:
\q1 Listen, I'm restoring the fortune of Yakov's \add (Jacob's)\add* \add ≈descendants\add*,
\q1 ≈and I will have compassion¦318452 on \add ≈the places where they live\add*.
\q1 \add ≈Each\add* city¦318454 will be rebuilt¦318453 on its mound¦318457,
\q1 ≈and \add ≈each\add* fortress¦318458 will sit on its proper¦318461 place¦318461.
